article.headline: Michigan 66, Wisconsin-Milwaukee 59
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) -- Courtney Sims scored 26 points to help Michigan defeat Wisconsin-Milwaukee 66-59 Wednesday in the final game of the John Thompson Challenge. Sims had 20 of those points in the second half to help the Wolverines hold off the pesky Panthers (1-3), who have lost three straight. He finished the game 10-for-13 from the floor and grabbed 10 rebounds. Avery Smith had 23 points and Paige Paulsen scored 13 for Milwaukee. The Panthers led 34-29 early in the second half, but Michigan (4-0) made six straight field goals during a 12-0 run that gave the Wolverines the lead for good. Milwaukee threatened to retake the lead several times in the last 10 minutes but never got over the hump. The Wolverines helped themselves by making 15 of their 24 field-goal attempts in the half. Neither team shot well from the field in the first half, but the Panthers were 5-for-7 from behind the arc. Smith's 3-pointer with a minute to play in the period gave Wisconsin-Milwaukee a 27-25 lead at the break. Dion Harris scored 17 points and Brent Petway added 13 for the Wolverines.
